<br>
Thornar Silverwood entered the great hall where he had pledged his devotion to all in times past. His heart was heavy and lump had found its way into his throat.<br>
   &quot;My Knights, you have been the force that has be with me over the years. We have seen many battles and many great victories in my time with you.&quot; <br>
The tears began to flow as he cleared his throat.<br>
   &quot;My heart is heavy these days my friends. The time has come and i must part from your side. My maker has set a different path for me and i must embark on this great quest as others have done before me&quot;.<br>
<br>
Thornar steadied himself and looked upon the glowing faces in the room. Thornar stood for a moment and watched as the shadows cast from the fire place danced about the walls of the room. Looking out upon them he walked toward the center of the room.<br>
   &quot;You have blessed me by allowing me to be in your presence thought be it just a glimer, I have seen your glourious deeds in action. Many of you i hold close to my heart and have placed life on the line for you, and you for me. These are the moments I will take with me as i now leave your side.&quot;<br>
<br>
Standing in the center of the room now the grief shown on his face, Thornar took off the tabard and held it in his hand as he lifted his arms to the heavens. Taking a deep claming breath thornar began.<br>
<br>
Do not let your heart be sad<br>
For to allow me to fight with you I am glad<br>
You made me into a great warrior, this i know<br>
And through you my soul did grow<br>
<br>
The time has come and i must depart<br>
For this, I will forever have a whole in my heart<br>
A quest set before me, and i must go<br>
Carry your honor i will, when times get low<br>
<br>
For all that i am and all i will be<br>
My faith, truth, and valor i pledge to thee<br>
Though a new chapter in my life has started<br>
Remember me always as Thornar the Pure Hearted.<br>
<br>
Thornar lowed his arms and began a slow lumber to the door. As the tears welled up in his eyes he thanked the knights for their faith and devotion. Thornar gave his tabard to kakras and grasped his arm firmly. <br>
   &quot;I was so privilged to wear your colors, i only hope that in my lifes travels i will make you proud my leige. <br>
<br>
Thornar made his way out of the hall donned his helm, sword, and climbed upon his holy stead. Glancing back toward the hall his horse reared up. Thornar rasied his sword and let lose a battle cry.<br>
   &quot;On your honor my knights&quot;<br>
With that thornar's horse galloped away into the dark night to fullfill his quest.<br>
<br>
God bless. <br>
